WEBVTT

00:01:26.490 --> 00:01:28.180
Shut up!

00:01:44.050 --> 00:01:45.690
Ow…

00:02:03.950 --> 00:02:04.750
W-Wha?

00:02:45.660 --> 00:02:46.630
Hey, Jet.

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:51.450
I’m asking ya, how much
longer before we land?

00:02:53.830 --> 00:02:55.960
How long ya been standing there?

00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:57.830
I’ve been here for a while.

00:02:57.870 --> 00:02:58.800
I see…

00:02:58.840 --> 00:03:00.970
What’re ya spacing out about?

00:03:01.010 --> 00:03:03.000
Where’s my bounty?

00:03:03.040 --> 00:03:07.810
Can’t you land quickly so I can
hand over that musty-looking fugitive?

00:03:07.850 --> 00:03:10.820
What, you haven’t even
gotten permission to land yet?

00:03:11.290 --> 00:03:14.580
I know. You guys are so obnoxious.

00:03:14.620 --> 00:03:17.520
Don’t rush so much!

00:03:17.560 --> 00:03:19.490
And take care of the
airport end for me.

00:03:21.760 --> 00:03:25.030
I thought Ganymede was your homeland.

00:03:25.070 --> 00:03:28.970
Were you perhaps thinking about some
woman in the past that cried over you?

00:03:34.680 --> 00:03:37.170
…or perhaps a woman
that made you cry.

00:03:37.710 --> 00:03:39.540
Didn’t ya hear me when I said
you’re being obnoxious?!

00:03:39.580 --> 00:03:41.710
<i>Yes…</i>

00:03:41.750 --> 00:03:43.340
<i>This is Ganymede police.</i>

00:03:45.750 --> 00:03:46.880
Donelly?

00:03:46.920 --> 00:03:49.820
<i>Oh, Jet! Jet, it’s you!</i>

00:03:49.860 --> 00:03:51.760
<i>There is no mistake…</i>

00:03:51.790 --> 00:03:55.630
<i>The top of your head’s gotten rather</i>
<i>lonely, but it’s still Jet all right!</i>

00:03:56.030 --> 00:03:58.220
Long time no see, Donelly.

00:03:58.270 --> 00:04:02.600
<i>I’m surprised that you’re working</i>
<i>around here. Has it been…</i>

00:04:02.640 --> 00:04:04.700
<i>Seven years? Eight?</i>

00:04:04.740 --> 00:04:07.260
<i>What the hell’s up with you</i>
<i>to come back so suddenly?</i>

00:04:07.670 --> 00:04:09.900
I wanna hand over a bounty.

00:04:09.940 --> 00:04:14.110
Wanted ad number EX41285.
Baker Panchorero.

00:04:16.120 --> 00:04:19.550
<i>To think you’re a bounty hunter…</i>

00:04:19.590 --> 00:04:22.110
<i>You, who was called the Black Dog…</i>

00:04:22.160 --> 00:04:24.750
<i>…a mad dog that never let</i>
<i>go of things bitten into?</i>

00:04:24.790 --> 00:04:28.160
I thought you had already retired.

00:04:28.200 --> 00:04:31.430
<i>Hey, I’m still an active officer!</i>

00:04:31.500 --> 00:04:35.430
<i>Don’t judge things on your time</i>
<i>scale, you Rip Van Winkle you.</i>

00:04:35.470 --> 00:04:39.460
—He used to be a cop? That explains…
<i>—That example is completely reversed!</i>

00:04:39.510 --> 00:04:41.140
—What?
<i>—I’m just glad to see yer still kickin’.</i>

00:04:41.140 --> 00:04:43.910
—…why I don’t get along with him.
<i>—Yeah, you, too.</i>

00:04:43.940 --> 00:04:47.440
<i>Oh yeah… what was her name…</i>

00:04:47.510 --> 00:04:49.410
<i>You know…</i>

00:04:49.450 --> 00:04:50.440
<i>I know! Alisa!</i>

00:04:52.030 --> 00:04:58.030
GANYMEDE ELEGY

00:04:58.790 --> 00:05:03.020
She’s got a little joint
in the port of Marvis.

00:05:03.060 --> 00:05:06.630
A small bar called “La Fin”…

00:05:06.630 --> 00:05:12.070
But in this recession, I hear
she’s got a lot of debts to pay…

00:05:12.110 --> 00:05:17.440
I’m sure there are a lot of problems
for a woman trying to live alone…

00:06:06.430 --> 00:06:08.830
Sense of justice and duty, huh?

00:06:08.860 --> 00:06:11.960
First time in a while he’s home,
of course he’s gonna go visit.

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.490
You’re totally wrong if you think
your old woman still thinks about you.

00:06:18.270 --> 00:06:22.400
You’re totally wrong yourself if you
think every other woman thinks like you.

00:06:22.440 --> 00:06:24.970
Justice and duty, duty,
three o’clock tea!

00:06:27.410 --> 00:06:28.940
Really, men…

00:06:34.520 --> 00:06:37.890
…are hopeless romantics.

00:06:40.290 --> 00:06:43.320
Hey, why are you
rubbing that stuff on?

00:06:43.960 --> 00:06:49.300
Beautiful skin is maintained by
continued effort that seems futile.

00:06:49.340 --> 00:06:50.770
Do you understand?

00:06:53.840 --> 00:06:57.000
I know! Futile! Useless!

00:07:14.130 --> 00:07:15.990
This is…

00:07:16.030 --> 00:07:18.330
…La Fin, right?

00:07:18.830 --> 00:07:20.820
Yeah… and you are?

00:07:23.100 --> 00:07:25.200
An old friend.

00:07:25.240 --> 00:07:27.230
I was in the area for
the first time in a while…

00:07:28.110 --> 00:07:30.470
Alisa… isn’t here.

00:07:32.410 --> 00:07:33.470
Jet?

00:07:35.450 --> 00:07:37.010
That can’t be…

00:07:37.050 --> 00:07:38.920
Are you really Jet?

00:07:40.790 --> 00:07:41.910
Rhint…

00:07:41.960 --> 00:07:45.050
…he is my guest.

00:07:45.090 --> 00:07:46.420
It’s all right.

00:07:52.170 --> 00:07:53.430
You don’t mind?

00:07:53.730 --> 00:07:55.200
I don’t…

00:07:55.240 --> 00:07:56.930
Anyway…

00:07:56.970 --> 00:07:59.530
How about it? You want a glass, right?

00:08:05.280 --> 00:08:07.910
You’re my last customer.

00:08:08.850 --> 00:08:10.080
I’m closing shop.

00:08:10.880 --> 00:08:14.340
The number of ships decreased,
and this area has gotten desolate…

00:08:14.390 --> 00:08:18.020
I’m thinking of moving to a new town.

00:08:18.060 --> 00:08:20.050
Are you all right?

00:08:20.560 --> 00:08:25.090
On the new island cities,
mortgage is expensive.

00:08:25.130 --> 00:08:26.860
Are you able to manage all that?

00:08:30.540 --> 00:08:34.500
That’s so like you to
worry about such things.

00:08:34.570 --> 00:08:37.540
I’m planning to change
myself in the new town.

00:08:37.580 --> 00:08:38.840
Don’t worry…

00:08:38.880 --> 00:08:40.850
Rhint is here with me…

00:08:43.820 --> 00:08:45.310
That guy that was just here?

00:08:45.650 --> 00:08:47.880
Something on your mind?

00:08:47.920 --> 00:08:49.010
Yeah.

00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:51.520
To tell the truth,
I already have 3 kids…

00:08:54.190 --> 00:08:56.560
I’m just kidding. It was a joke!

00:08:56.600 --> 00:08:59.390
Rhint is just my boyfriend.

00:08:59.430 --> 00:09:01.560
How are you doing?

00:09:01.600 --> 00:09:02.860
Have you gotten married yet?

00:09:03.040 --> 00:09:06.730
I live and wander with
a group of weirdos.

00:09:06.770 --> 00:09:09.140
And on top of it,
I’m a bounty hunter now.

00:09:19.250 --> 00:09:20.650
Do you remember?

00:09:27.690 --> 00:09:29.030
<i>Where’s Jet?</i>

00:09:29.060 --> 00:09:31.030
Doing personal stuff.

00:09:31.060 --> 00:09:33.160
<i>You’re his partner, right?</i>

00:09:33.200 --> 00:09:35.260
Yeah.

00:09:35.300 --> 00:09:38.290
<i>I’ve got news on a bounty,</i>

00:09:38.340 --> 00:09:41.030
<i>This hasn’t been</i>
<i>publicly broadcast yet…</i>

00:09:44.610 --> 00:09:46.640
<i>Rhint Celonius.</i>

00:09:46.680 --> 00:09:49.480
<i>A thug in the port of Marvis.</i>

00:09:49.520 --> 00:09:52.710
<i>Last night, he contacted</i>
<i>financial broker Law Rentzuo.</i>

00:09:52.750 --> 00:09:55.850
<i>This guy was another tough guy…</i>

00:09:55.920 --> 00:09:57.580
<i>…but he was killed!</i>

00:09:57.890 --> 00:10:00.220
And so?

00:10:00.330 --> 00:10:03.630
<i>Rhint… is Alisa’s gigolo.</i>

00:10:04.160 --> 00:10:06.060
<i>I thought I’d warn you guys.</i>

00:10:08.300 --> 00:10:10.460
And how much is the bounty?

00:11:16.540 --> 00:11:20.070
Back then…
when I got home from work…

00:11:20.070 --> 00:11:22.480
You always waited for me.

00:11:22.480 --> 00:11:25.040
That was all I needed.

00:11:29.380 --> 00:11:31.320
But that day…

00:11:35.860 --> 00:11:39.760
When I came home,
only that watch was left…

00:11:40.690 --> 00:11:45.630
…and a small note with
one word: “farewell”.

00:11:47.600 --> 00:11:52.000
For some reason, I didn’t feel sad.

00:11:52.540 --> 00:11:56.340
It just lacked reality.

00:11:57.610 --> 00:12:04.110
And I gradually felt something
inside me go numb…

00:12:06.650 --> 00:12:09.350
After 6 months,
I made a bet with myself.

00:12:09.920 --> 00:12:14.550
That I would leave this
planet if you didn’t return…

00:12:16.130 --> 00:12:18.860
…by the time this clock stopped.

00:12:20.500 --> 00:12:23.040
I didn’t come here to blame you.

00:12:23.040 --> 00:12:26.200
I just wanted to know…

00:12:27.440 --> 00:12:30.530
…why you disappeared back then.

00:12:33.450 --> 00:12:39.650
You seem to think that
time on Ganymede had stopped.

00:12:42.420 --> 00:12:44.820
That’s a story from long ago…

00:12:47.030 --> 00:12:50.330
I’ve… forgotten it.

00:12:53.730 --> 00:12:56.000
I don’t need time that stands still.

00:12:57.800 --> 00:13:00.100
Farewell, Jet…

00:14:04.570 --> 00:14:08.300
A bounty hunter? Then can he be?

00:14:09.180 --> 00:14:10.140
Rhint…

00:14:10.180 --> 00:14:12.200
He’s after me…

00:14:12.280 --> 00:14:15.680
I have a bounty on my head…

00:14:17.580 --> 00:14:20.140
It’s all over!

00:14:21.990 --> 00:14:23.820
It’s not your fault.

00:14:23.860 --> 00:14:29.060
It’s because I borrowed
money from a guy like him…

00:14:29.100 --> 00:14:32.230
…and you protected me…

00:14:32.230 --> 00:14:34.790
I can’t be saved if I get caught.

00:14:34.830 --> 00:14:37.390
I…

00:14:37.440 --> 00:14:39.630
…killed a guy…

00:14:41.670 --> 00:14:42.640
Let’s get outta here…

00:14:44.880 --> 00:14:46.610
Let’s get outta here,
just the two of us!

00:15:17.180 --> 00:15:20.240
This must be because
I have good karma…

00:15:24.850 --> 00:15:26.180
Sorry, but it’s business.

00:15:42.400 --> 00:15:43.700
Steer for me, please!

00:16:19.570 --> 00:16:21.230
<i>Hey? What’s wrong?!</i>

00:16:21.270 --> 00:16:23.440
I’m after a bounty worth 1.8 million.

00:16:23.480 --> 00:16:25.910
—<i>What?!</i>
<i>—Here, I’ll send it to you.</i>

00:16:27.510 --> 00:16:29.240
He’s a bounty?

00:16:29.280 --> 00:16:35.310
<i>Yeah, a secret bit of info from Donelly,</i>
<i>He apparently killed a loan shark.</i>

00:16:36.020 --> 00:16:36.820
Dammit!

00:16:43.100 --> 00:16:45.330
<i>I’ll do this. You can go back.</i>

00:16:47.730 --> 00:16:50.330
You’re not gonna let him go, are ya?

00:16:50.370 --> 00:16:52.770
<i>This is the land where I was a cop…</i>

00:16:53.540 --> 00:16:56.240
I’m the Black Dog…
Once I bite, I never let go.

00:16:58.880 --> 00:17:02.940
I have no regrets about her, but I’ll
settle this score on my home turf.

00:17:04.580 --> 00:17:06.980
Sense of justice and duty, huh…

00:17:12.730 --> 00:17:13.590
<i>Can you hear me…?</i>

00:17:14.790 --> 00:17:16.520
<i>Stop the boat, now!</i>

00:17:17.300 --> 00:17:18.520
Jet?

00:19:25.590 --> 00:19:28.080
Stay away!

00:19:29.700 --> 00:19:31.290
Please, let us go!

00:19:35.030 --> 00:19:38.490
There are other bounties to find!

00:19:40.110 --> 00:19:45.270
Even if I let you go,
someone will come for you someday…

00:19:45.310 --> 00:19:47.310
If you run, you will
become an accomplice.

00:19:47.310 --> 00:19:48.370
Stay away!

00:19:50.080 --> 00:19:51.850
You still have time.

00:19:51.880 --> 00:19:53.820
Don’t worry about me anymore!

00:20:07.830 --> 00:20:09.300
You were like this back then, too…

00:20:11.100 --> 00:20:13.330
You decided everything.

00:20:13.370 --> 00:20:16.340
And you were always right…

00:20:16.380 --> 00:20:20.970
When I was with you,
I never had to do anything.

00:20:21.010 --> 00:20:27.040
All I had to do was hang on to your arm
like a child, with no cares in the world.

00:20:28.720 --> 00:20:33.280
I wanted to decide how to
live my life by myself…

00:20:34.230 --> 00:20:38.030
Even if that was a mistake…

00:20:54.780 --> 00:20:57.650
Let go! I don’t wanna
go to prison! Let go!!

00:20:58.250 --> 00:21:00.650
Help! Help me, please!

00:21:07.690 --> 00:21:09.760
Be strong…

00:21:09.760 --> 00:21:12.790
…and protect her…

00:21:28.280 --> 00:21:31.840
Self-defense seems to
be how they see it.

00:21:35.250 --> 00:21:37.450
What are you going to do now?

00:21:37.490 --> 00:21:40.390
I won’t be going anywhere anymore.

00:21:41.160 --> 00:21:44.060
I will wait in my store… for Rhint.

00:21:45.360 --> 00:21:47.960
It won’t take long…

00:21:48.000 --> 00:21:51.600
…because time is flowing along.

00:22:27.890 --> 00:22:33.320
Aishiteta to nageku niwa…
Too much time has passed by…

00:22:33.360 --> 00:22:39.660
…amarinimo toki wa sugite shimatta
…to lament that we were deeply in love.

00:22:39.700 --> 00:22:45.360
Mada kokoro no hokorobi wo…
The wind keeps blowing, while my heart…

00:22:45.400 --> 00:22:52.100
…iyasenu mama kaze ga fuiteru
…cannot heal all the tears in it.

00:22:52.140 --> 00:23:01.350
Kawaita hitomi de dareka naite kure
Someone, cry for me with parched eyes.

00:23:02.950 --> 00:23:06.360
The real folk blues.

00:23:06.360 --> 00:23:14.770
Honto no kanashimi ga shiritai dake
I only want to know what true sadness is.

00:23:14.800 --> 00:23:22.400
Doro no kawa ni tsukatta…
Sitting in muddy water…

00:23:22.440 --> 00:23:26.900
…jinsei mo waruku wa nai…
…isn’t such a bad life…

00:23:26.940 --> 00:23:35.820
…ichido kiri de owaru nara…
…if it ends after the first time…

00:23:51.620 --> 00:23:51.840
COMING EPISODE

00:23:51.840 --> 00:23:52.710
An unseen terror
assaults the Bebop crew.
COMING EPISODE

00:23:52.710 --> 00:23:56.280
An unseen terror
assaults the Bebop crew.

00:23:56.310 --> 00:24:01.180
Caught by the venomous fangs of the
unseen enemy, another victim falls.

00:24:01.220 --> 00:24:06.950
What is the identity of the fearsome
enemy that refuses to show itself?

00:24:06.990 --> 00:24:11.620
A symphony of shivers that will send
you into the deepest trenches of terror!

00:24:11.660 --> 00:24:15.260
Next episode: “Toys in the Attic.”

00:24:15.330 --> 00:24:17.690
Once the channel is set,
you will no longer be able to escape…

00:24:17.690 --> 00:24:20.690
